Simply being able to raise up the suspension to tackle some light offloading is exactly why I chose the Urus S over the Performante. The air suspension on the Urus S is significantly more compliant and versatile compared to the fixed steel springs in the Performante, unless you actually plan on tracking the Urus the S is the way to go… I will say that the Performante’s stance is a little nicer than the S though… what are your thoughts? 😈

Love seeing my projects come to reality. Designing and developing properties is so rewarding because the journey truly is as beautiful as the destination. I can’t believe it’s been six years since I opened up @theluxedesignstudio. We went from doing a few minor restaurant renovations annually  to multiple multi-million dollar projects monthly! I can’t wait to see what the future holds. Honestly for any young gun out there, dream big, stay focused and you truly can achieve anything in life. I designed this lakeside mansion at 25 years old, never did I think I would be able to acquire projects like this back then! Welcome challenges, don’t be scared! Nothing good comes easy. Now it’s time to grow @slabform_interiors the way we grew LUXE. 🙏

Honoured to have been interviewed by the new neighbourhood magazine, Neighbors of Shaughnessy. This magazine is now being distributed to 2,000+ homes in the first and second Shaughnessy area and features interviews with noteworthy residents, local businesses and services! It’s been amazing hearing about all of the other amazing residents and I am truly honoured for them to choose me for the cover. @theluxedesignstudio has been growing in the Shaughnessy area and I can’t wait to see where 2024 takes us! 🙏
What a year… ups downs and everything in between! Cheers to a 2024 filled with happiness, success and nothing less! 🥂
